    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document describes the JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) text sequence format and associated media type "application/json-seq".  A JSON text sequence consists of any number of JSON texts, all encoded in UTF-8, each prefixed by an ASCII Record Separator (0x1E), and each ending with an ASCII Line Feed character (0x0A).&lt;/p&gt;</t>
